RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHISKY WARRIOR was reserved in the rear, started closing the gap after the seventh hurdle, edged clear in the stretch and prevailed driving. TIGER TO REMEMBER vied for the lead, finished strong but was outpaced. BLESS BLESS was in contention throughout, was unable to reach the top two, but finished well. GREYLOVER vied for the lead early but gave way. WORLD OF FOOLS was no factor, dropped back but got around and eased after the last hurdle. MERKABA was never a factor, tired and pulled up before the last hurdle.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TRYON RACE 3 2M Hurdle CR: N/A. Claiming Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs. Claiming price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEIZING THE DREAM ran evenly, stalked the leaders, made a bid with purpose after the eighth hurdle and prevailed. TOP BRASS (GB) kept pace but failed to quicken under pressure. RACE.RACE_TEXT: TRYON RACE 4 2M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 120 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GORDON'S JET (IRE) tracked the leader, rallied before the last hurdle, and led throughout the stretch. ANIMAL KINGSTON settled, made a closing move after the eighth hurdle with good effort but was outfinished in the stretch. POTUS settled in the back and made a late gain to close the gap. JIMMY P raced in the middle of the pack and failed to quicken. TEASE AND SEIZE (FR) set the pace early but weakened before the final hurdle. MOLLY FANTASY (GER) ran evenly and was never a threat. UCO VALLEY (IRE) was up with the pace early, tired, and pulled up before the last hurdle. TOPIC CHANGER trailed the field on a wide trip, tired, and pulled up before the last hurdle.
